NAME
    Task::Perl::Critic - Install everything Perl::Critic.

VERSION
    This document describes Task::Perl::Critic version 1.8.0.

SYNOPSIS
    This module does nothing but act as a placeholder. See Task.

DESCRIPTION
    This module does nothing but act as a placeholder. See Task.

    WARNING: Installing this distribution will install Policies that
    directly conflict with each other. If you do not use a .perlcriticrc
    file, and your severity is set high enough, there is no way for your
    code to not have violations. A specific example:
    Perl::Critic::Policy::Compatibility::ProhibitThreeArgumentOpen and
    Perl::Critic::Policy::InputOutput::ProhibitTwoArgOpen directly
    contradict each other.

INTERFACE
    None.

DIAGNOSTICS
    None.

CONFIGURATION AND ENVIRONMENT
    Task::Perl::Critic requires no configuration files or environment
    variables.

DEPENDENCIES
    Perl::Critic

    Test::Perl::Critic

    Test::Perl::Critic::Progressive

    criticism

    Perl::Critic::Bangs

    Perl::Critic::Compatibility

    Perl::Critic::Dynamic

    Perl::Critic::Itch

    Perl::Critic::Lax

    Perl::Critic::Moose

    Perl::Critic::More

    Perl::Critic::Nits

    Perl::Critic::PetPeeves::JTRAMMELL

    Perl::Critic::Pulp

    Perl::Critic::Storable

    Perl::Critic::StricterSubs

    Perl::Critic::Swift

    Perl::Critic::Tics

INCOMPATIBILITIES
    None reported.

BUGS AND LIMITATIONS
    No bugs have been reported.

    Please report any bugs or feature requests to
    "bug-task-perl-critic@rt.cpan.org", or through the web interface at
    <http://rt.cpan.org>.

